comments: Butler (MIA) deflects the ball into the ball into the backcourt and Bridges (PHX) legally regains possession.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Bridges' (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Strus (MIA) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Ayton (PHX) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Booker (PHX) contests Lowry's (MIA) jump shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs after his release.
Payne (PHX) and Martin (MIA) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Payne (PHX) is bracing for the contact from Martin (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Ayton (PHX) hands off the ball in Martin's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs as Martin defends under the pick.
Ayton (PHX) re-establishes himself slightly in Butler's (MIA) path and avoids making contact with Butler during the screen.
Lowry (MIA) grabs and holds Craig's (PHX) arm off ball and the contact restricts his ability to move freely.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.  The ensuing lower body contact is caused by Booker.
Booker (PHX) (PHX) abruptly extends his leg towards Butler (MIA) and marginal contact occurs after he has released his jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) and Martin (MIA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Butler (MIA) brings his forearm towards Craig (PHX) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away to secure the pass.
Payne (PHX) is moving alongside Lowry's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Payne (PHX) makes contact with the ball as he defends Lowry's (MIA) driving shot attempt.
Butler (MIA) briefly grasps Craig's (PHX) arm underneath the basket and releases in pursuit of the loose ball.
Butler (MIA) places his hand momentarily on Booker's (PHX) side and marginal contact occurs as they move in the same direction.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Martin's (MIA) path and absorbs the contact.
Booker (PHX) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Bridges's (PHX) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Bridges's (PHX) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Adebayo (MIA) is already in Bridges' (PHX) path and he absorbs the contact to his upper body.
Ayton (PHX) initiates contact to Adebayo's (MIA) wrist at the start of his upward shooting motion and the contact affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Booker (PHX) establishes himself in Adebayo's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Lowry (MIA) places his hands against Craig (PHX) during the screen and marginal contact occurs as they disengages.
Craig (PHX) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Lowry (MIA) during the screen.
Adebayo (MIA) moves forward into Booker's (PHX) space and delivers contact that dislodges Booker from his legally obtained position.
Butler (MIA) immediately slides his hand off of Booker's (PHX) side and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Strus's (MIA) path and firming up when contact occurs.
Martin (MIA) is moving alongside Payne's (PHX) path and marginal lower body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Ayton (PHX) places his hand momentarily on Adebayo's (MIA) side and he removes his hand as they pursue the rebound.
Strus (MIA) brushes Ayton's (PHX) arm after he has secured possession, and the contact is marginal.
Adebayo (MIA) brushes Ayton's (PHX) arm and marginal contact occurs after Ayton has released the ball to pass.

Butler (MIA) applies a stayed forearm to Booker's (PHX) body and he immediately removes his forearm as Booker begins his upward shooting motion.  Butler then proceeds to cleanly block Booker's jump shot attempt.
Butler (MIA) is moving alongside Booker's (PHX) path and absorbs the contact as the two come together at the same spot.
Booker (PHX) is bracing for the contact from Butler (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as Booker releases away from the contact.
Butler (MIA) applies a rested forearm to Booker's (PHX) body and he immediately removes his forearm as Booker enters his upward shooting motion.
